<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,678,1027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis box="[151,212,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">Adult</emphasis>
. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[348,474,679,703]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" unit="mm" value="20.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="18.0">18–22 mm</quantity>
. Adults are very similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[903,982,678,703]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eilema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,982,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">Eilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: forewing narrow, gray˗fuliginous, pale gray, pale yellow, or pale brown, but the former can be distinguished by lacking the contrasting light costal margin typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[266,345,750,775]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eilema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[266,345,750,775]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">Eilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male genitalia: uncus more or less stout, with a small spine at apex. Valvae asymmetrical, with cucullus simple, pointed apically, and sacculus with a characteristic broadening subapically on right valva and more acute on left valva. Juxta elongated with a long sclerotized process, symmetrically bifurcated and flattened or tubular and asymmetrically greatly extended on one side. Aedeagus short, stout. Vesica with few large cone˗shaped cornuti, sometimes with an added distal spine˗like cornutus, and a series of smaller cornuti or spiniculi fields. Female genitalia: female genitalia with ovipositor short and stout; large ostium funnel heavily sclerotized and variable sclerotizations in the ductus bursae; ductus seminalis very large and usually spiraled; corpus bursae with paired, small scobinated signa patches.
</paragraph>
